'''Dave Holmes''', [[Registered nurse|RN]], [[Ph.D.]], is a [[Canada|Canadian]] [[professor]] of [[nursing]], [[researcher]], and [[author]] based in [[Ottawa]], [[Ontario]], [[Canada]]. His research interests and writing are in the areas of [[Public Health]], [[Forensic nursing|Forensic Nursing]], [[Critical Theory]], [[Epistemology]], Law and Ethics, [[Psychiatric and mental health nursing|Psychiatric Nursing]], Nursing in Corrections, Socio-political Aspects of Nursing, [[Human sexuality|Sexuality]], and [[Public health nursing|Public Health Nursing]].

== Biography ==
Professor Holmes earned his bachelor's degree in [[Nursing]] from the [[University of Ottawa]] in 1991, his [[M.Sc.]] in Nursing from the [[Universit<U+00E9> de Montr<U+00E9>al]] in 1998, and his Ph.D. in Nursing from the Universit<U+00E9> de Montr<U+00E9>al in 2002. In 2003, he completed a [[CIHR]] post-doctoral fellowship in Health Care, Technology and Place at the [[University of Toronto]], Faculty of Social Work, and he has been principal investigator on CIHR- and [[SSHRC]]-funded research projects on risk management in the fields of Public Health and Forensic Nursing. Most of Professor Holmes<U+2019>s work and research is based on the poststructuralist works of [[Deleuze]] & [[Guattari]] and [[Michel Foucault]]. He has presented at many national and international conferences.

Professor Holmes teaches post-graduate nursing theory, forensic nursing, and policy courses at universities in Ottawa, [[Montr<U+00E9>al]], and [[Pittsburgh]]. In 2014, he held the following main positions:
* University Research Chair in Forensic Nursing<ref name="UofOChair">{{cite web |url=http://www.health.uottawa.ca/chair_forensic_nursing/index.htm |title=University of Ottawa - Faculty of Health Sciences - University Research Chair in Forensic Nursing|publisher=University of Ottawa |accessdate=31 December 2013}}</ref> (2009-2019), University of Ottawa, Faculty of Health Sciences, School of Nursing
* Full Professor, Director, and Associate Dean, University of Ottawa, Faculty of Health Sciences, School of Nursing
* Editor-in-Chief, ''Aporia - the Nursing Journal''<ref name=APORIA>{{cite book|last=Holmes|first=Dave|title=Aporia, the Nursing Journal|publisher=University of Ottawa|location=Ottawa, Ontario, Canada|isbn= |issn=1918-1345 |pages=|url=http://www.oa.uottawa.ca/journals/aporia/about_aporia.jsp|edition=|coauthors=O<U+2019>Byrne, Patrick; Perron, Am<U+00E9>lie; and St-Pierre, Isabelle  (eds.)|accessdate=1 January 2014}}</ref>

Professor Holmes is or has been an Honorary Visiting Professor at the [[University of Indonesia]], [[Jakarta]], [[Indonesia]] (2013-2016); Fort de Kock College of Health Sciences, [[West Sumatra]], Indonesia (2013-2016); Binawan Institute of Health Sciences,<ref name=BIHS>{{cite web|title=Binawan Institute of Health Sciences|url=http://www.binawan-ihs.ac.id|accessdate=5 January 2014}}</ref>  Jakarta, Indonesia (2013-2016); the [[University of Chester]], Faculty of Health and Social Care, [[Chester]], United Kingdom (2008-2011/2011-2014); and [[City University]], School of Community and Health Sciences, [[London]], United Kingdom (2008-2013). He was a visiting scholar at the [[University of Sydney]], Faculty of Nursing, [[Sydney]], Australia, in 2008, and has been an Honorary Visiting Scholar at [[Flinders University]], School of Nursing and Midwifery, [[Adelaide]],  [[Australia]] (2006) and [[Duquesne University]], School of Nursing, Pittsburgh, [[Pennsylvania]], [[United States]] (1999).

== Works ==
Professor Holmes has co-edited 3 books:
* ''(Re)Thinking Violence in Healthcare Settings: A Critical Perspective'',<ref>{{cite book|last=Holmes|first=Dave|title=(Re)Thinking Violence in Healthcare Settings: A Critical Perspective|year=2012|publisher=Ashgate|location=Farnham, Surrey, U.K.|isbn=9781409432661|pages=|url=http://www.ashgate.com/isbn/9781409432661|edition=|coauthors=Rudge, Trudy, & Perron, Am<U+00E9>lie|accessdate=31 December 2013}}</ref> [[Ashgate Publishing|Ashgate]], 2012;
* ''Abjectly Boundless: Bodies, Boundaries, and Health Work'',<ref>{{cite book|last=Holmes|first=Dave|title=Abjectly Boundless: Bodies, Boundaries, and Health Work|year=2010|publisher=Ashgate|location=Farnham, Surrey, U.K.|isbn=9780754679103|pages=|url=http://www.ashgate.com/isbn/9780754679103|edition=|author2=Rudge, Trudy|accessdate=31 December 2013}}</ref> Ashgate; 2010, and
* ''Critical Interventions in the Ethics of Health Care'',<ref>{{cite book|last=Murray|first=Stuart J.|title=Critical Interventions in the Ethics of Health Care|year=2009|publisher=Ashgate|location=Farnham, Surrey, U.K.|isbn= 9780754673965 |pages=|url=http://www.ashgate.com/isbn/9780754673965|edition=|author2=Holmes, Dave|accessdate=31 December 2013}}</ref> Ashgate, 2009.

He has also authored over 100 articles in peer-reviewed journals, 33 book chapters, 19 other peer-reviewed articles, 10 non-peer-reviewed articles, and 9 conference abstracts/proceedings. He has spoken at 30 peer-reviewed conferences and has been invited to speak at over 30 conferences. Some representative examples of Professor Holmes's more important articles and book chapters:
* ''Insufficient" but still "necessary"? EBPM's dangerous leap of faith''<ref>{{cite journal|last=Holmes|first=Dave|author2=Murray, Stuart J. |author3=Perron, Am<U+00E9>lie |title="Insufficient" but still "necessary"? EBPM's dangerous leap of faith|journal=International Journal of Nursing Studies|year=2009|volume=46|issue=5|pages=749<U+2013>750|url=http://modernrhetoric.files.wordpress.com/2010/11/11756934300511838175.pdf|accessdate=3 January 2014|doi=10.1016/j.ijnurstu.2009.01.011|pmid=19217106}}</ref>
* ''MS3 Squad: Considering Cyborgs for Future Prevention Programs''<ref>{{cite journal|last=Holmes|first=Dave|coauthors=O<U+2019>Byrne, Patrick, and Coyte, P.|title=MS3 Squad: Considering Cyborgs for Future Prevention Programs|journal=Body, Space, & Technology|year=2007|issue=8|pages=9<U+2013>16|url=http://www.academia.edu/945778/MS3_Squad_Considering_Cyborgs_for_Future_Prevention_Programs|accessdate=3 January 2014}}</ref>
* ''Nursing in Corrections: Lessons from France''<ref>{{cite journal|last=Holmes|first=Dave|coauthors=Perron, Am<U+00E9>lie, and Michaud, Gabrielle|title=Nursing in Corrections: Lessons from France|journal=Journal of Forensic Nursing|year=2007|volume=3|issue=3<U+2013>4|pages=126<U+2013>131|issn=1939-3938|publisher=[[Wiley-Blackwell|Wiley]]|doi=10.1111/j.1939-3938.2007.tb00098.x|pmid=18027532}}</ref>
* ''Deconstructing the Psychopath: A Critical Discursive Analysis''<ref>{{cite journal|last=Federman|first=Cary|coauthors=Holmes, Dave, and Jacob, Jean Daniel|title=Deconstructing the Psychopath: A Critical Discursive Analysis|journal=Cultural Critique|year=2009|volume=Spring|issue=72|pages=36<U+2013>65|publisher=University of Minnesota Press|jstor=25619824|doi=10.1353/cul.0.0037}}</ref>
* ''Practice to Evidence and Evidence to Practice: Misunderstanding the Epistemic Incommensurability''<ref>{{cite journal|last=Holmes|first=Dave|author2=Gagnon, M.|title=Practice to Evidence and Evidence to Practice: Misunderstanding the Epistemic Incommensurability|journal=Journal of Evaluation in Clinical Practice <U+2013> International Journal of Public Health Policy and Health Services Research|year=2008|volume=14|pages=663<U+2013>664|publisher=[[Wiley-Blackwell|Wiley]]|issn=1365-2753|doi=10.1111/j.1365-2753.2008.01092.x|issue=5}}</ref>
